Package: pgtools
Type: Package
Title: Standardized Workflow for Writing Tables to PostgreSQL
Version: 0.1.0
Author: person("Eugene", "Joh", email = "johe@smh.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Eugene Joh <johe@smh.ca>
Description: This package provides a standardized workflow to write R data frames into a PostgreSQL database. Wrapper functions based on the `DBI` and `RPostgres` packages allow the user to identify field types and varying lengths for elements.
    This has only be tested for PostgreSQL 9.5.
License: GPL (>=3)
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
  readr,
  purrr,
  tibble,
  dplyr,
  magrittr,
  glue,
  DBI,
  RPostgres (>= 1.1.1),
  usethis
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
Suggests: 
    testthat
